<li id="cite_note-Trewhitt1984-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Trewhitt1984_10-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFTrewhitt1984" class="citation book cs1">Trewhitt, Katharine L. (1984). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=dwvrAAAAMAAJ"><i>History of Broad Street United Methodist Church, Cleveland, Tennessee, 1836-1984: The Story of Methodism in Bradley County and of the Group which Became Broad Street United Methodist Church</i></a>. The Church. p.&#160;129<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">8 July</span> 2017</span>. <q>In 1968 the Methodist Men of Broad Street purchased flags to be used in the sanctuary of the Church. This involved one United States flag, one Christian flag, flag poles, stands, one eagle and one cross.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=History+of+Broad+Street+United+Methodist+Church%2C+Cleveland%2C+Tennessee%2C+1836-1984%3A+The+Story+of+Methodism+in+Bradley+County+and+of+the+Group+which+Became+Broad+Street+United+Methodist+Church&amp;rft.pages=129&amp;rft.pub=The+Church&amp;rft.date=1984&amp;rft.aulast=Trewhitt&amp;rft.aufirst=Katharine+L.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DdwvrAAAAMAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChristian+Flag" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAalberts2021" class="citation web cs1">Aalberts, Leon (2021). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://firstchurchwilliamstown.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/18-April-2021-Chatter.pdf">"Flags in the Sanctuary"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <a href="/wiki/Williamstown,_Massachusetts" title="Williamstown, Massachusetts">Williamstown</a>: First Congregational Church. p.&#160;5<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">23 September</span> 2021</span>. <q>Since its adoption by the United States Federal Council of Churches in 1942, it has been used by many Christian traditions, including the Anglican, Baptist, Lutheran, Mennonite, Methodist, Moravian, Presbyterian, Quaker, and Reformed, among others.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Flags+in+the+Sanctuary&amp;rft.place=Williamstown&amp;rft.pages=5&amp;rft.pub=First+Congregational+Church&amp;rft.date=2021&amp;rft.aulast=Aalberts&amp;rft.aufirst=Leon&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Ffirstchurchwilliamstown.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F18-April-2021-Chatter.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChristian+Flag" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Achtemeier2016-12"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Achtemeier2016_12-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAchtemeier2016" class="citation web cs1">Achtemeier, Katherine (1 July 2016). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://pres-outlook.org/2016/07/flags-in-worship/">"Flags in worship"</a>. The Presbyterian Outlook<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">23 September</span> 2021</span>. <q>For as long as anyone could remember, the American flag had been displayed in the front of the sanctuary to the congregation's left — to their right, the Christian flag.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Flags+in+worship&amp;rft.pub=The+Presbyterian+Outlook&amp;rft.date=2016-07-01&amp;rft.aulast=Achtemeier&amp;rft.aufirst=Katherine&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fpres-outlook.org%2F2016%2F07%2Fflags-in-worship%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChristian+Flag" class="Z3988"></span></span>
