<li id="cite_note-26"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.presbyterianmission.org/ministries/worship/faq/faq-signssymbols/">"Presbyterian Mission Agency Signs and symbols"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Presbyterian_Church_(USA)" title="Presbyterian Church (USA)">Presbyterian Church (USA)</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">9 January</span> 2018</span>. <q>If a national flag is used alongside a symbol of God's realm (such as the popularly accepted "Christian flag," found mostly in U.S. congregations), the Christian flag is appropriately given a preeminent place.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Presbyterian+Mission+Agency+Signs+and+symbols&amp;rft.pub=Presbyterian+Church+%28USA%29&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.presbyterianmission.org%2Fministries%2Fworship%2Ffaq%2Ffaq-signssymbols%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChristian+Flag" class="Z3988"></span></span>
