<li id="cite_note-SJR2021-28"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-SJR2021_28-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.stjohnrussell.com/history.html">"History of St. John Lutheran Church"</a>. St. John Lutheran Church<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">23 September</span> 2021</span>. <q>Feelings of patriotism to the church characterized the period of World War II, 1940 – 1945.  The American and Christian flags were presented to the church at this time.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=History+of+St.+John+Lutheran+Church&amp;rft.pub=St.+John+Lutheran+Church&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.stjohnrussell.com%2Fhistory.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChristian+Flag" class="Z3988"></span></span>
