<li id="cite_note-1917Grose-29"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-1917Grose_29-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-1917Grose_29-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGrose1917" class="citation book cs1">Grose, Howard Benjamin (1917). <i>Missions: American Baptist International Magazine, Volume 8</i>. American Baptist Convention. p.&#160;497.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Missions%3A+American+Baptist+International+Magazine%2C+Volume+8&amp;rft.pages=497&amp;rft.pub=American+Baptist+Convention&amp;rft.date=1917&amp;rft.aulast=Grose&amp;rft.aufirst=Howard+Benjamin&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChristian+Flag" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation book cs1"><i>Fifty-Eighth Annual Session</i>. <a href="/wiki/Order_of_the_Eastern_Star" title="Order of the Eastern Star">Order of the Eastern Star</a>. 1932. <q>Today the Christian Flag is flying over Europe, Asia and Africa, as well as America.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Fifty-Eighth+Annual+Session&amp;rft.pub=Order+of+the+Eastern+Star&amp;rft.date=1932&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChristian+Flag" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Diffendorfer1917-31"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Diffendorfer1917_31-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFDiffendorfer1917" class="citation book cs1">Diffendorfer, Ralph Eugene (1917). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/MN41415ucmf_0"><i>Missionary Education in Home and School</i></a>. Abingdon Press. p.&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.org/details/MN41415ucmf_0/page/n213">184</a>. <q>The Christian flag is not patented, and is free from commercialism. Anyone may manufacture it, and it may be used on all proper occasions. Christian flags may be displayed at conventions, conferences, church demonstrations, and parades, and with the American flag may be used for general decorative purposes. For boys' and girls' societies and clubs and for the church school, especially on program occasions, the two flags may be presented and saluted.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Missionary+Education+in+Home+and+School&amp;rft.pages=184&amp;rft.pub=Abingdon+Press&amp;rft.date=1917&amp;rft.aulast=Diffendorfer&amp;rft.aufirst=Ralph+Eugene&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Farchive.org%2Fdetails%2FMN41415ucmf_0&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChristian+Flag" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-32"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBrown2016" class="citation web cs1">Brown, Drew (25 March 2016). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.vice.com/en_ca/article/5gq4da/newfoundlands-government-flies-a-christian-flag-low-key-holy-war-follows">"Newfoundland's Government Flies a 'Christian Flag,' Low-Key Holy War Follows"</a>. <a href="/wiki/Vice_(magazine)" title="Vice (magazine)">Vice</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">9 January</span> 2018</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Newfoundland%27s+Government+Flies+a+%27Christian+Flag%2C%27+Low-Key+Holy+War+Follows&amp;rft.pub=Vice&amp;rft.date=2016-03-25&amp;rft.aulast=Brown&amp;rft.aufirst=Drew&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vice.com%2Fen_ca%2Farticle%2F5gq4da%2Fnewfoundlands-government-flies-a-christian-flag-low-key-holy-war-follows&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChristian+Flag" class="Z3988"></span></span>
